## 🔄 Workflow Sequences

### Startup Sequence

```
1. Chrome Debug Port Verification
   ├─ Check IPv6: curl -6 http://localhost:9222/json/version
   └─ Check IPv4: curl -4 http://localhost:9222/json/version

2. BrowserManager Initialization
   ├─ Auto-detect IPv6/IPv4 endpoint
   └─ Establish CDP connection

3. Authentication Verification
   ├─ Check existing session
   └─ Login if required (supplier-specific)

4. Configuration Loading
   ├─ Load system_config.json
   ├─ Load supplier categories
   └─ Initialize EnhancedStateManager

5. State Analysis
   ├─ Load processing_state.json
   ├─ Calculate resume point
   └─ Validate frozen denominators
```

### Category Processing Sequence

```
For each category in poundwholesale_categories.json:

1. URL Discovery & Manifest Generation
   ├─ Scrape category page for all product URLs
   ├─ Save complete URL list atomically to manifest
   └─ Freeze denominator (write-once, never changes)

2. Category Initialization
   ├─ Initialize with frozen denominator
   ├─ Setup progress tracking
   └─ Handle empty categories (denominator=0)

3. Product Processing Loop
   For each product:
   ├─ Resume pointer validation
   ├─ Supplier data extraction
   ├─ Amazon analysis (EAN-first, title fallback)
   ├─ Financial calculations
   └─ Atomic state commit
```

### Interruption & Resume Sequence

```
INTERRUPTION (Ctrl+C, crash, network loss)
         │
         ▼
Atomic State Persistence
├─ WindowsSaveGuardian ensures write completion
├─ Resume pointer saved as {phase, cat_idx, prod_idx}
└─ All files validated before commit
         │
         ▼
RESUME (System restart)
├─ Load processing_state.json
├─ Reconstruct progress from linking_map.json
├─ Validate frozen denominators unchanged
└─ Continue from last saved pointer
```

